item.dc:creator: @davidi2 Davidi2
item.description:
@davidi2 wrote:

[quote=“The Chubby Bunny, post:1, topic:328232”]I’m using netbeans IDE 6.8
I have this in my code:

int[] itemSlots = new int[4];
  
  itemSlots[0] = -1;
  itemSlots[1] = -1;
  itemSlots[2] = -1;
  itemSlots[3] = -1;
  itemSlots[4] = -1;

And I’m getting this error in netbeans:

']' expected

Is there anything wrong with the code, or does netbeans have a bad attitude?[/quote]
Are you an idiot? Arrays are the second thing you learn when starting Java. Even Abraham knows about them!

When you declare the confines of the array you do not declare the highest index, you declare the number of values.

int[] itemSlots = new int[4];
There are four integers in the array.

itemSlots[0] = -1; itemSlots[1] = -1; itemSlots[2] = -1; itemSlots[3] = -1; itemSlots[4] = -1;
I count 5. If you see otherwise then you must be blind AND retarded.
